            <title>[STORM-3729] Assigning memory greater and equal than 2048m will make assgin memory for slot values to 1m</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STORM-3729</link>
                <project id="12314820" key="STORM">Apache Storm</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, everyone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I set my topology over 2048m, the storm ui shows only 65m, so i found its error in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/storm/blob/master/storm-client/src/jvm/org/apache/storm/utils/Utils.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/storm/blob/master/storm-client/src/jvm/org/apache/storm/utils/Utils.java&lt;/a&gt;&#160; line 1089 that value cast to int instead of long, It goes wrong if I pass 2048m and results 1m.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simply change this line to cast Long can solve this problem.&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
